 A truck and a light motor vehicle were involved in a head-on collision and eleven other people were injured. It was believed that one of the two vehicles was pulling a trailer with fruit, which was scattered over the scene. The N4 eastbound had to be closed for two and a half hours last night. The deceased has not yet been identified. Three women and eight men were passengers on the bakkie, which collided head on with the truck. The truck driver wasn’t injured and says the bakkie veered into his lane from the opposite side. The driver of the bakkie was killed upon impact.     The ferals need help #TrafficAlert: R555 closed, seven die in horrific crash Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za